How do tell Controller Method to Check for Spring Security Roles
----------------------------------------------------------------



Procedure
---------
 If your ControllerMethod returns a ModelAndView, then use this code

      if (! aRequest.isUserInRole("Admin"))
      {
          // Return the error back to the caller
          throw new AccessDeniedException("You don't have the Admin role");
      }
      
      

If your Controller Method returns a ResponseEntity, then use this code:
 
 
